Make sure the mpicc commands are in your path. Most likely the permissions are too restrictive on the commands. Make sure they&#39;re all group/world read &amp; execute (I set them with chmod 755 ...)<div><br></div><div>As for XCode, I cheat. Since I build multi-platform, I use CMake or SCons. In one case, I setup XCode as an external compile project, and then use scons as the compile command. And since you&#39;re using &quot;import&quot; you must be compiling in Objective-C, of which, I can provide no assistance (c/c++/python).</div>
