</div><div>Thanks!</div><div><div class="h5"><div><br></div><br><div><div>On Nov 12, 2012, at 7:29 AM, Mark Bolstad wrote:</div><br><blockquote type="cite">You may want to see if you have MacPorts installed. Typically (but not always), /opt/local is from a MacPorts installation. If it is then it&#39;s very easy to remove mpich and install openmpi.<div>
<br></div><div>To check for MacPorts, see if /opt/local/bin/port exists. Then,</div>
<div><br></div><div>sudo port uninstall --follow-dependencies mpich2</div><div>sudo port install openmpi</div><div><br></div><div>FYI, I&#39;m using OpenMPI 1.6 with XCode 4.5.2 on 10.8.2 and it works fine. </div><div><br>

